      <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
         <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
         <p>Beryl Graves (Hodge) is the wife of English poet and author Robert Graves. Their relationship started in 1940 and continued until his death.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Consists of personal records and correspondence pertaining to Laura (Riding) Jackson, collected by Beryl Graves. The correspondence includes letters exchanged between Laura (Riding) Jackson and a variety of corespondents, including Schuyler B. Jackson, publishers Arthur Barker and Constable, and Nancy Cunard. There are also several letters to Robert Graves.</p>
      </scopecontent>
